Coronavirus has left many South Africans living in fear as drastic restrictions imposed to help avoid widespread. Amid all the cases confirmed in the country, there have been some enormous blunders by officials that have had social media. Here are some of the blunders: 1. The newly appointed spokesperson of the Department of Sports, Arts and Culture, Masechaba Ndlovu has had to issue an apology after mistakenly tweeting that South African people were dying from coronavirus. A mistake many social media users did not let slide in her first few days in office. 2. This hilarious reaction from razzmatazz left the internet in stitches. This time around Aaron Motsoaledi, the Minister of Home Affairs coughs during a press briefing and Fikile Mbalula is not having it. 3. While the Minister of Health, Dr Zweli Mkhize was briefing the media in Bloemfontein on Friday, an official was seen touching their face while putting on gloves. An error that left many wondering if health officials had adequate hygiene education. 4. Dr Anban Pillay the DG of the Department of Health reacts to swiftly Minister Dr Zweli Mkhize's cough.  5. The Minister of Social Development, Lindiwe Zulu was slammed on Saturday for video making light of coronavirus. On the clip Minister Zulu said she was struggling of staying at home and that coronavirus must go away.  